<div class="about-page">
  <h1>About MyShop Dashboard</h1>

  <div class="notice-box trademark-disclaimer">
    <p>The term "Etsy" is a trademark of Etsy, Inc. This application uses the Etsy API but is not endorsed or certified by Etsy, Inc.</p>
  </div>

  <p>MyShop Dashboard is a personal tool designed to help independent Etsy sellers get a clear, unified view of their shop's performance — orders, listings, and analytics — all in one place.</p>

  <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Node.js 20</strong> — server runtime</li>
    <li><strong>Express 4</strong> — web framework</li>
    <li><strong>EJS</strong> — server-side templates</li>
    <li><strong>Chart.js 4</strong> — data visualisation</li>
    <li><strong>Lucide</strong> — icon library</li>
    <li>No database — mock data in Phase 1</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Privacy</h2>
  <div class="notice-box">
    <p>This tool runs entirely on your own server. No data is sent to third parties. In Phase 1, all data is mock/demo data. When connected to the Etsy API (Phase 2), your shop data stays on your machine.</p>
  </div>

  <p class="disclaimer"><em>This is a personal developer tool, not an official Etsy product. Use at your own risk.</em></p>
</div>
